    <section id="love-a-mug">
        <h2>Love-a-Mug</h2>
        <p><em>Mug off single-use cups and love a reusable mug.</em></p>
        <p>We froth sustainability – so thanks a latte for helping people and the planet one mug at a time. Our pollution solution? A hug in a mug!</p>
        <h3>Here’s the tea:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Single-use cups contain plastic lining and PFAS forever chemicals</li>
            <li>They harm the environment – releasing greenhouse gases for thousands of years</li>
            <li>They harm human health – hormone disruptors and microplastics</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Australia:</strong> 1.5 billion single-use coffee cups a year – that’s thousands every second.</p>
        <h3>How we work:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Mugs donated from City Mission</li>
            <li>Tub buckets to hold mugs</li>
            <li>Potential collaborations & proceeds back to charity</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Cleaning:</h3>
        <p>We’re exploring industrial washer options ($5–10k), and partnerships with churches, hotels, or markets.</p>
        <div class="impact-box">
            <h3>CO₂e Savings Tracker</h3>
            <p>Every time you use a second-hand mug instead of a disposable coffee cup, you avoid approximately <strong>0.025 kg CO₂e</strong>.</p>
            <p>Our community has already avoided <strong>50,000 disposable cups</strong>, saving about <strong>1.25 tonnes CO₂e</strong>.</p>
        </div>
        <h3>QR Code Actions:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Accept T&Cs</li>
            <li>Donate via Apple Pay to fund dishwashers, volunteers, and mugs</li>
            <li>Sign petitions to strengthen single-use bans</li>
            <li>Follow us on Instagram</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Our Social Enterprise Goals:</h3>
        <p>We lobby for a ban on single-use and PLA cups in our community. We promote slowing down, sitting down for coffee, and appreciating the moment. We collaborate with pottery makers and grow the mug library movement.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="about-us">
        <h2>About Us</h2>
        <p>We started this project to make reuse the norm. We’re eco-warriors, coffee lovers, and community builders turning small changes into big impacts. Every mug saved from landfill is a win for the planet.</p>
    </section>

